e they return. Worse still, they&#8217;re often surprised to find that many of the problems that drove them too use in the first place are there waiting for them when arrive back home. It can be tough to remember your new-found coping skills once outside of the comfortable\u00a0boundaries\u00a0of a <a title=\"rehab\" href=\"\/why-pathways\/\">rehab<\/a> center. And this is what can lead to relapse.<\/p>\n<h2>How Pathways Is Different<\/h2>\n<p>Pathways Real Life works for you and <em>with<\/em> you.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Unlike Inpatient programs, Pathways sends a counselor directly to your home.<\/strong>\u00a0Your therapy takes place where you are most relaxed. Rather than being surrounded by a group of strangers in a cold, clinical hospital setting, you can snuggle comfortably in your favorite chair or surrounded by a cherished pet or loved one. Instead of feeling forced into a new way of life, you become a Free Agent. You make all the decisions and together with your drug treatment counselor, life coach, family therapist (or anyone else you may need), you design a plan that works best for you &#8211; and you alone.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-252 aligncenter\" title=\"Customized Drug Treatment Program in Salt Lake City, Utah - Pathways Real Life Recovery in Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/01\/couple.jpg\" alt=\"Happy Couple - Customized Drug Treatment in Salt Lake City\" width=\"620\" height=\"465\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/01\/couple.jpg 620w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/01\/couple-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2>What About Family Members?<\/h2>\n<p>As part of our holistic approach, Pathways&#8217; counseling program involves family members as well. Your family will be trained to act as your recovery suppo